The World Bank said it approved a 25mln dlr structural adjustment loan for Mauritius to aid thatcountry's industrial sector.    The Bank said the 17-year loan will support policy reformsdesigned to help increase the efficiency of the country'smanufacturing sector, develop export enterprises and encourageefficient use of resources.    It added, "The increased availability of foreign exchangefor imports is expected to help the expansion of industrialoutput and exports." Reuter&#3;